Healthcare workers getting ready for the COVID-19 vaccine rollout. eNCA/Masego Rahlaga JOHANNESBURG - The Health Department reported 4,424 new COVID-19 cases over the last 24 hours. A total of 93 more deaths take South Africa's death toll to 56,170. READ: Mediclinic expects COVID-19 vaccine delivery SA's recovery rate is 93,8 percent. The total number of recorded cases in the country to more than 1.6-million. A family meeting could soon be called as President Cyril Ramaphosa met with the National Command Council on Tuesday. Meanwhile, Cabinet says its discussing measures to be taken to slow the rising number of COVID-19 infections. As of today the cumulative number of #COVID19 cases identified in SA is 1 649 977, with 4 424 new cases reported. Today 93 deaths have been reported which brings the total to 56 170 deaths. The cumulative recoveries now stand at 1 548 092 representing a recovery rate of 93, 8% pic.twitter.com/TtWuGdz8uc